The forecast shows a gradual warming pattern and high pressure building over the area, bringing above-normal temperatures this weekend. Far inland temperatures are expected in the 80s to low 90s, while coastal temperatures will be in the mid-60s. Several locations have minor to moderate heat risks, and people are encouraged to increase intake of water, take breaks in shade, check on the elderley and never leave pets or children inside locked vehicles. Winds are expected to be moderate to light throughout. A Small Craft Advisory is in effect.